<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT AND MAIN BEARINGS (RECONDITIONING) - OIL PAN REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>OIL PAN REMOVAL</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Effective with S/N 532981 and thru S/N 594857, all engines are equipped with an oil pan sump
                    acoustic cover to reduce noise levels in accordance with government standards. The four cover
                    spacers are attached as shown in Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150726">7.26</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Effective with S/N 568680 all engines are equipped with a magnetic drain plug.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the oil pan as follows:</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The oil pan must be removed prior to removing the flywheel housing due to the studs in the
                        housing which are used to retain the oil pan.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove four long oil pan bolts and washers from the rear of the oil pan (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150727">7.27</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the remaining oil pan bolts, washers and cover spacers.</para>
                <figure id="ef4150726" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12527" filename="../figcg1/CG12527.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.26. Oil Pan Cover Spacer Mounting Locations.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150727" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11893" filename="../figcg1/CG11893.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.27. Remove Oil Pan Fasteners.</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Effective with Serial Number 593721 oil pans have been installed using a
                            robotically-applied liquid gasket.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove oil pan and gasket from the crankcase. Discard the gasket. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_146.xml" xrefid="ef4150728">7.28</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
